VERSE 4
[04:50.17]And he arose and came to his father
[04:57.23]But when he was a great way off, his father saw him
[05:04.22]And had compassion, and ran, and fell on his neck
[05:11.19]And kissed him and then he said
[05:17.97]Bring forth a robe, and put it on
[05:24.54]Put a ring on his finger and get some shoes
[05:31.12]Bring the fatted calf, lets kill it; and eat, and let us be merry
[05:38.68]For my son was dead, is now alive
[05:41.92]He was lost, and now is found
